
[1]pliant

   PLI'ANT, a. That may be easily bent; readily yielding to force or
   pressure without breaking; flexible; flexile; lithe; limber; as a
   pliant thread.

   1. That may be easily formed or molded to a different shape; as pliant
   wax.

   2. Easily yielding to moral influence; easy to be persuaded; ductile.

   The will was then more ductile and pliant to right reason.
